0in%20terms%20of%20literacy%20rate%20in%20the%20country.%20Lakshadweep%20Administration%E2%80%99s%20recent%20decision%20to%20discontinue%20the%20Kerala%20syllabus%20in%20both%20English%20and%20Malayalam%2C%20and%20to%20migrate%20all%20students%20to%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Secondary%20Education%20pattern%2C%20has%20reopened%20the%20age-old%20debate%20on%20an%20indigenous%20curriculum%20in%20Lakshadweep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20literacy%20rate%20of%2018.33%25%20in%201951%20to%2070.04%25%20in%202011%2C%20India%20has%20made%20significant%20progress%20on%20this%20front.%20However%2C%20this%20mission%20of%20educating%20the%20masses%20has%20failed%20to%20address%20cultural%20and%20geographical%20sensitivities%20across%20the%20country%2C%20including%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%2C%20Lakshadweep%2C%20and%20tribal%20areas%20in%20Kerala.%20They%20all%20received%20education%20with%20the%20same%20mainland%20curriculum.%20In%20Lakshadweep%2C%20education%20currently%20means%20adopting%20a%20syllabus%20borrowed%20from%20Kerala%2C%20with%20no%20separate%20curriculum%20for%20Lakshadweep%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20website%20of%20Lakshadweep%20provides%20a%20concise%20history%20of%20formal%20education%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20first%20government%20school%20in%20Amini%20was%20established%20in%201904%2C%20and%20the%20first%20person%20graduated%20from%20Lakshadweep%20in%201942.%20The%20first%20two%20high%20schools%20were%20set%20up%20in%20the%201960s%20in%20Amini%20and%20Kalpeni%2C%20respectively.%20Now%2C%20all%20the%20islands%2C%20except%20Bitra%2C%20have%20secondary-level%20schools%2C%20showcasing%20robust%20infrastructure%20with%20good%20buildings%20and%20adequate%20teachers.%20Bitra%20also%20has%20schools%20up%20to%20the%208th%20standard.%20As%20a%20UT%2C%20Lakshadweep%20has%20received%20ample%20funding%20for%20educational%20infrastructure%2C%20supported%20by%20central%20government%20schemes%20like%20Samagra%20Shiksha%20Abhiyan%20(SMSA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20higher%20education%20in%20Lakshadweep%20has%20not%20been%20a%20focus%20area%20for%20the%20administration.%20Even%20though%20two%20Calicut%20University%20centres%20were%20established%20in%20Androth%20and%20Kadamath%2C%20most%20students%20in%20Lakshadweep%20depend%20on%20Kerala%20for%20higher%20studies.%20Calicut%20University%20has%20reserved%20one%20seat%20for%20one%20subject%20in%20every%20college%20in%20Kerala.%20Since%202020%2C%20when%20former%20Gujarat%20home%20minister%20Praful%20Patel%20took%20charge%20as%20the%20Administrator%20of%20Lakshadweep%2C%20changes%20in%20the%20education%20sector%20have%20been%20notable.%20The%20administration%20closed%20down%20Calicut%20University%20centres%20and%20started%20government%20colleges%20under%20Pondicherry%20University%20in%20Kadamath%20and%20Androth.%20Additionally%2C%20a%20government%20Polytechnic%20College%20in%20Minicoy%20and%20a%20government%20Nursing%20College%20in%20Kavaratti%20were%20established.%20However%2C%20the%20infrastructure%20and%20functioning%20of%20these%20colleges%20have%20been%20controversial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudent%20protests%20erupted%20in%202022%2C%20with%20students%20from%20the%20Colleges%20in%20Kadamath%20and%20Minicoy%20going%20on%20an%20indefinite%20strike.%20Instead%20of%20improving%20infrastructure%2C%20the%20administration%20banned%20protests%20in%20the%20colleges.%20Many%20students%20are%20still%20suffering%20from%20the%20migration%20to%20Pondicherry%20University%20from%20Calicut%20University.%20According%20to%20Iqbal%2C%20a%20student%20leader%20from%20the%20Kadamath%20campus%2C%20nearly%20hundreds%20of%20students%20have%20lost%20a%20year%20as%20proper%20certificates%20have%20not%20been%20distributed%20to%20them%20after%20completing%20the%20course%20from%20Pondicherry%20University.%20They%20are%20planning%20to%20file%20a%20writ%20petition%20at%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20against%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Flakshadweep-disability-rights-activists-hold-another-protest-as-accessibility-issues-continue%5C%22%3ELakshadweep%3A%20Disability%20Rights%20Activists%20Hold%20Another%20Protest%20as%20Accessibility%20Issues%20Continue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20attempted%20to%20shut%20down%20many%20schools.%20While%20the%20decision%20to%20close%20Junior%20Basic%20Schools%20in%20Kadamath%20and%20Chetlath%20was%20stayed%20by%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%2C%20some%20schools%20such%20as%20the%20Southern%20Junior%20Basic%20School%20and%20Northern%20Junior%20Basic%20School%20in%20Kiltan%20have%20already%20closed.%20Both%20schools%20have%20been%20merged%20into%20one%20Junior%20Basic%20School%2C%20as%20the%20existing%20Senior%20Basic%20School%20has%20been%20merged%20with%20the%20high%20school.%20Recent%20decisions%20without%20planning%20or%20preparation%20have%20resulted%20in%20public%20outrage%20and%20student%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20uproar%20over%20shifting%20students%20and%20school%20closures%2C%20the%20department%20of%20education%20issued%20an%20order%20to%20migrate%20all%20Lakshadweep%20students%20to%20the%20CBSE%20pattern%20within%20two%20years.%20Implementing%20this%20order%20will%20end%20the%20more%20than%2070-year-old%20educational%20system%20in%20Lakshadweep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala-based%20syllabus%20uses%20Malayalam%20as%20a%20medium%20of%20instruction.%20While%20CBSE%20is%20already%20taught%20in%20schools%2C%20students%20currently%20have%20a%20choice%20between%20the%20Kerala%20curriculum%20and%20that%20of%20the%20CBSE.%20When%20this%20order%20is%20implemented%2C%20this%20choice%20will%20cease%20to%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMP%20Mohammed%20Faizal%20wrote%20to%20the%20education%20minister%20as%20well%20as%20the%20home%20minister%2C%20seeking%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20decision.%20Kerala%20education%20minister%2C%20V.%20Sivankutty%2C%20also%20wrote%20to%20the%20Union%20education%20minister%20Dharmendra%20Pradhan%2C%20seeking%20the%20same.%20He%20questioned%20the%20National%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%20and%2C%20in%20a%20video%20posted%20on%20his%20Facebook%20page%2C%20said%20that%20while%20the%20NEP%20talks%20about%20increasing%20options%2C%20bureaucrats%20in%20Lakshadweep%20have%20denied%20this%20choice%20to%20students%20by%20discontinuing%20the%20Kerala%20pattern%20of%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20between%20CBSE%20and%20the%20Kerala%20pattern%20will%20continue%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20in%20the%20education%20sector%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Lakshadweep%20is%20complicated%20and%20goes%20beyond%20this%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20languages%20spoken%20in%20Lakshadweep%20%E2%80%93%20one%20is%20Jasari%2C%20spoken%20in%20nine%20inhabited%20islands%2C%20and%20the%20other%20is%20Diwehi%20which%20is%20spoken%20in%20only%20one%20island%2C%20Minicoy.%20Jasari%20has%20no%20script%20and%20its%20similarity%20to%20the%20Dravidian%20languages%20made%20it%20vulnerable.%20The%20language%20almost%20lost%20its%20identity%20due%20to%20the%20islands%E2%80%99%20long%20encounter%20with%20the%20Kerala%20pattern%20of%20education%20which%20uses%20Malayalam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20native%20writers%20started%20writing%20back%20to%20assert%20the%20identity%20of%20Jasari%20as%20the%20language%20of%20Lakshadweep.%20The%20first%20novel%20written%20by%20Thakiyudheen%20from%20Kiltan%20island%20in%20Jasari%2C%20named%20%3Cem%3EFadappurappad%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20using%20the%20Malayalam%20script%2C%20has%20already%20been%20published.%20Ironically%2C%20this%20book%20has%20been%20published%20years%20after%20the%20publishing%20of%20%3Cem%3EKolodam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20first%20Malayalam%20novel%20from%20Lakshadweep%20written%20by%20Ismath%20Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiwehi%20is%20a%20dialect%20of%20Mahal%2C%20a%20language%20spoken%20in%20the%20Maldives.%20As%20far%20as%20people%20from%20Minicoy%20are%20concerned%2C%20every%20language%20is%20a%20foreign%20language%3B%20we%2C%20the%2010%2C000%2B%20people%20in%20the%20country%2C%20speak%20this%20language.%20We%20are%20more%20familiar%20with%20Hindi%20than%20Malayalam.%20%E2%80%9CStudying%20Malayalam%20as%20a%20language%20will%20also%20help%20us%20as%20nowadays%20ships%20are%20connected%20only%20to%20Kerala%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20F.G.%20Mohammed%2C%20a%20retired%20government%20servant%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Information%20and%20Public%20Relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFousiya%2C%20a%20post%20doctoral%20student%20at%20IIT%20Kanpur%20who%20hails%20from%20Minicoy%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20prefer%20English%20as%20a%20medium%20of%20study%20over%20Malayalam%2C%20but%20studying%20it%20as%20a%20language%20will%20help%20students%20learn%20one%20more%20language%20as%20a%20choice.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20need%20for%20a%20localised%20syllabus%20is%20more%20important%20than%20this%20debate.%20We%20study%20about%20oceans%20and%20the%20Himalayas%20in%20schools%3B%20instead%2C%20we%20should%20include%20more%20about%20our%20culture%20and%20geography%20in%20the%20textbooks%20so%20that%20at%20least%20the%20next%20generation%20will%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20islands%20in%20the%20perspective%20of%20conservation%20and%20also%20in%20cultural%20as%20well%20as%20historic.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0Lakshadweep%2C%20we%20are%20trying%20to%20fit%20a%20square%20peg%20of%20democratic%20decision-making%20into%20a%20bureaucratic%20round%20hole.%20Administration%20in%20Lakshadweep%20is%20a%20single%20line%20and%20controlled%20by%20the%20centralised%20power%20called%20Administrator%20appointed%20by%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnilateral%20decisions%20without%20consultation%20are%20a%20characteristic%20of%20a%20bureaucratic%20system%20of%20governance.%20Rakesh%20Dahiya%2C%20a%20Delhi%2C%20Andaman%2C%20Nicobar%20Islands%2C%20Lakshwadeep%2C%20Dadra%20Nagar%20Haveli%20and%20Daman%20Diu%20Administrative%20Service%20(DANICS)%20officer%2C%20has%20unilaterally%20decided%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Lakshadweep%20with%20a%20single%20signature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20of%20migration%20of%20all%20the%20students%20was%20taken%20without%20consultation%20with%20any%20of%20the%20stakeholders.%20Students%2C%20parents%2C%20even%20the%20school%20management%20committee%20were%20not%20aware%20of%20this%20drastic%20decision.%20A%20system%20that%20accommodates%20people%E2%80%99s%20views%20and%20is%20open%20to%20wide%20consultation%20and%20deliberation%20is%20the%20only%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%20is%20closing%20down%20schools%20or%20migration%20of%20students%20to%20CBSE%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20based%20on%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20people.%20Being%20a%20democratic%20country%2C%20we%20cannot%20legislate%20or%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20a%20group%20of%20people%20without%20their%20consent.%20Unfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESalahuddin%20is%20a%20researcher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703757020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F27095308%2Flakshadweep-boats.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Flakshadweep-students-face-bureaucratic-battle-over-curriculum-claim-no-discussion-with-stakeholders%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Being%20a%20democratic%20country%2C%20we%20cannot%20legislate%20or%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20a%20group%20of%20people%20without%20their%20consent.%20Unfortunately%2C%20that%20is%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20islands.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Flakshadweep-students-face-bureaucratic-battle-over-curriculum-claim-no-discussion-with-stakeholders%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%